# UIUX: rich-text-editor

## Goal
A rich text editor that feels native on Windows. WYSIWYG editing with Markdown
as storage format. Real-time rendering via Skia/skparagraph. Live preview of
MCP-driven mutations with amber highlight that fades after 2 seconds.

## Platform
- OS: Windows 11
- Toolkit: Slint (via slint-ui-templates — Fluent 2 design system)
- Icons: Segoe Fluent Icons (from slint-ui-templates)
- Backdrop: Mica or Solid (via slint-ui-templates platform module)

## UI Foundation Rules
Load these via get_rule() before any UI work.

| Rule | What it enforces |
|------|-----------------|
| uiux/tokens.md | Zero literal values in components — all values from slint-ui-templates tokens |
| uiux/components.md | One file per component, one responsibility |
| uiux/file-structure.md | Folders by feature area |
| uiux/state-flow.md | State-in from adapter, events-out |
| uiux/menus-slint.md | Slint menu patterns |
| uiux/menus-windows.md | Windows platform menu conventions |
| uiux/help-about.md | About dialog, license, shortcuts |
| uiux/checklist.md | Pre-ship verification |

## UI Architecture
- Toolkit: Slint + slint-ui-templates desktop shell
- Entry point: ui/main.slint
- Shell: imported from slint-ui-templates (AppWindow, NavBar, SideBar, StatusBar)
- Editor canvas: custom component using Slint render notifier for Skia rendering
- Toolbar: formatting toolbar (bold, italic, code, heading, list, media)
- Status bar: word count, cursor position, document stats

## Component Conventions
- All visual values from slint-ui-templates tokens (Theme, Sizes, Durations)
- Component names PascalCase, match filename (EditorCanvas -> EditorCanvas.slint)
- Slint components handle only: toolbar clicks, keyboard events, window size
- All text rendering done in Skia render notifier, not in Slint components
- MCP mutation highlight: amber background (#EF9F2720) with 2s fade animation

## User Flows

### Primary Flow: Edit Document
1. User opens .md file -> parsed to AST, rendered via skparagraph
2. User clicks in text -> cursor placed via getGlyphPositionAtCoordinate
3. User types -> InsertTextCommand via UndoStack -> re-layout affected paragraph
4. User selects text -> getRectsForRange highlights selection
5. User clicks formatting button -> FormatRangeCommand via UndoStack

### Secondary Flow: MCP Editing
1. Claude Desktop sends tool call (e.g. replace_range)
2. MCP server applies command via UndoStack
3. UiEvent::BlockChanged sent to Slint thread
4. Affected block re-renders with amber highlight
5. Highlight fades after 2 seconds
6. document://current resource notified

### Secondary Flow: Media Insertion
1. User or MCP inserts image/video path
2. Block::Image/Video added to AST
3. skparagraph addPlaceholder() reserves space
4. MediaManager loads asset asynchronously
5. Thumbnail rendered on placeholder rect via getRectsForPlaceholders

## Layout

### Main Window
- Shell: slint-ui-templates AppWindow (NavBar + Content + StatusBar)
- Content area: EditorCanvas (full Skia render notifier surface)
- Toolbar: formatting toolbar above editor canvas
- Status bar: word count, character count, cursor offset

## Interaction Patterns
- Loading: status bar spinner for async operations
- Errors: status bar message for transient, dialog for permanent
- Undo: Ctrl+Z in GUI, undo tool in MCP — both use same UndoStack
- Selection: click-drag or Shift+arrow, double-click for word boundary
- Scroll: vertical scrollbar, mouse wheel, page up/down

## Accessibility
- All toolbar buttons reachable by keyboard
- Tab order: toolbar left-to-right, then editor canvas
- Focus ring always visible
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 for text (enforced by slint-ui-templates theme)
